## 1. Project Overview

Friday is a Python desktop assistant inspired by Iron Man's F.R.I.D.A.Y. It combines a futuristic UI, voice control, internet awareness, and controlled system automation with strict file-access blocking.

**Repository name suggestion:** friday-assistant  
**License:** MIT

---

## 2. Features

- PySide6 neon HUD interface with chat panel
- Wake-word voice: "Friday"
- Background listener launches app when closed
- Text command input
- DuckDuckGo search (no API key)
- RSS news headlines (BBC, Reuters, NPR, Al Jazeera)
- Open-Meteo weather (no API key)
- Chrome / Brave browser control
- App allowlist launcher
- Policy engine blocks all file access
- PyInstaller EXE packaging
- Windows login auto-start for listener

