## 5. Voice and Wake Word

### In-app voice
Runs while Friday window is open. Listens for wake word then captures command.

### Background listener
Process: `pythonw -m friday.background_listener`
- Hears "Friday" when app is closed
- Launches or focuses Friday window
- Queues command via `~/.friday/pending_command.txt`

### Config keys
```json
"voice": {
  "wake_word": "friday",
  "always_listen_for_wake": true,
  "launch_on_wake_word": true,
  "start_listener_at_login": true
}
```

---

## 6. Configuration

File: `%USERPROFILE%\.friday\config.json`

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| user_name | Greeting name |
| voice.wake_word | Wake phrase |
| browser.preferred | chrome or brave |
| web.default_city | Weather default |
| app_allowlist | Apps Friday can open |
| site_shortcuts | URL shortcuts |

---

## 7. Safety Policy

Friday ALWAYS blocks:
- File/folder read, write, open, list
- Drive paths (C:\, D:\, etc.)
- file:// URLs
- cmd, PowerShell, Explorer
- Shutdown, uninstall, registry

Enforced in `friday/policy/guardrails.py` before any command runs.

